I'll solve this step-by-step, calculating the various financial ratios based on the given financial statements.

## 1. Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Capital Expenditures
FCF = -224,133.22 - 106,218.20 = -330,351.42

## 2. Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = Net Income / Average Total Assets
Average Total Assets = (Initial Assets + End Assets) / 2 = (13,000,000 + 15,023,526.85) / 2 = 14,011,763.43
ROA = 1,193,771.08 / 14,011,763.43 = 0.0852 = 8.52%

## 3. Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = Net Income / Average Shareholder's Equity
Average Shareholder's Equity = (Initial Equity + End Equity) / 2 = (13,000,000 + 14,193,771.08) / 2 = 13,596,885.54
ROE = 1,193,771.08 / 13,596,885.54 = 0.0878 = 8.78%

## 4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio
Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Net Income
Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = -224,133.22 / 1,193,771.08 = -0.19

## 5. Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = Net Income / Total Revenue
Net Profit Margin = 1,193,771.08 / 5,695,115.02 = 0.2096 = 20.96%

## 6. Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue
Gross Profit Margin = 2,610,115.02 / 5,695,115.02 = 0.4583 = 45.83%
